id.kaytrust.core.credential.ethereum.client

Class EthereumCredentialValidationImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • id.kaytrust.core.credential.ethereum.client.EthereumCredentialValidationImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CredentialValidation, EthereumCredentialValidation

    public class EthereumCredentialValidationImpl
extends Object
implements EthereumCredentialValidation
    This class implements the methods that are performed in order to check if a credential has been correctly issued by some entity/person/organization. This class is compliant with any any ethereum network.

    Here is an example of a verifiable credential format: 

     
 {
   "@type": "VerifiableCredential",
   "@context": "https://schema.org",
   "credentialSubject": {
     "@id": "did:example:abcd",
     "name": "John Doe",
     "birthdate": "2018-01-01"
   },
   "issuer": "did:ev:2uukHPBYMjdZPkg4p5ZjipKHzkaXLr4T5ut",
   "proof": {
       "type": "EthereumAttestationRegistry2019",
       "contractAddress": "0x123f681646d4a755815f9cb19e1acc8565a0c2ac",
       "networkId": "0x19"
     }
 }
    Verifiable credentials are compliant with W3C
    Author:
    Edgard Espinoza, Erick Pacheco
